        {
          "name": "context",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "An SSL session context reference."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "connection",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "An SSL session connection reference. The connection data is opaque to Secure Transport; you can set it to any value that your application can use to uniquely identify the connection in the callback functions "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/security/sslreadfunc"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " and "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/security/sslwritefunc"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ". "
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "return_value",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Return Value",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A result code. See "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/security/1503828-secure_transport_result_codes"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You must establish a connection before creating a secure session. After calling the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/security/1393063-sslcreatecontext"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " function to create an SSL session context, you call the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/security/1398843-sslsetconnection"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " function to specify the connection to which the context applies. You specify a value in the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "connection"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " parameter that your callback routines can use to identify the connection. This value might be a pointer to a socket (if you are using the Sockets API) or an endpoint (if you are using Open Transport). For example, you might create a socket, start a connection on it, create a context reference, cast the socket to an "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/security/sslconnectionref"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", and then pass both the context reference and connection reference to the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/security/1398843-sslsetconnection"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " function."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Note that the Sockets API is the preferred networking interface for new development."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "On the client side, it’s assumed that communication has been established with the desired server on this connection. On the server side, it’s assumed that a connection has been established in response to an incoming client request ."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This function must be called prior to the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/security/1400161-sslhandshake"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " function; consequently, this function can be called only when no session is active."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
